\nThe Los Angeles metropolitan area, also known as Metropolitan Los Angeles or the Southland,http://abclocal.go.com/kabc/story?section=news/local/los_angeles&id=7319588  is the 13th largest metropolitan area in the world and the second-largest metropolitan area in the United States.http://geography.about.com/od/lists/a/csa2005.htm  It is entirely located in the southern portion of the U.S. State of California.